-- 
BRAZIL DAYBOOK: Industrial Production in June, Usiminas Earnings

-- B y   R o b i n   S t r i n g e r
-- 
2011-08-02T03:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-02/brazil-daybook-industrial-production-in-june-usiminas-earnings.html
Industrial production  likely fell 0.4
percent in  Brazil  during June, according to the median estimate
of 30 economists surveyed by Bloomberg. The country’s national
statistics agency IBGE releases the figures at 9 a.m.  Usiminas, Brazil’s second-biggest steelmaker, reports
second-quarter results after the market close.  GOVERNMENT:
*Central bank President Alexandre Tombini attends the start of
ValorInvest at the Bovespa in Sao Paulo at 10:15 a.m. and
attends a lunch with Gruppo Esponenti Italiani at 12:30 p.m.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Petrobras CEO Jose Sergio Gabrielli speaks about the oil
company’s 2011-2015 business plan in  New York , starting at 11
a.m. Brasilia time.  ECONOMY:
*Industrial production MoM and YoY at 9 a.m.  EARNINGS:
*Usiminas (USIM5 BZ) before market.
*Itau (ITUB4 BZ)
*Tim (TCLS4 BS) after market.  EQUITIES:
*BR Malls (BRML3 BZ) may be included in the Bovespa index
starting next month, according to the first preview of the index
components.
*Petrobras (PETR4 BZ) said its Franco oil field holds about 4
billion barrels of recoverable oil and natural gas.
*Duratex (DTEX3 BZ) reported second-quarter profit of 91.1
million reais.  MARKETS
*The Bovespa index fell 0.5 percent to 58,535.74.
*The real fell 1.1 percent to 1.5661 per dollar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
